General distribution. This water strider species occurs throughout the Oriental Region with records from Pakistan (known western limit of the species), India , Nepal , Sri Lanka , Bangladesh , Myanmar , Thailand , Laos , Vietnam , China ( Hainan ), Malaysia (peninsular and Borneo), Singapore , and Indonesia ( Sumatra ) (see
Damgaard et al. 2014
).

Remarks. This species was recorded from Punjab by Pruthi (1933) . More recently, it was recorded from Keenjhar Lake in Sindh Province (
Buzzetti et al. 2006
), which is about 1000 km south-southwest of the study area.
